This paper is primarily focused on image retrieval, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories. The paper also introduces a novel regional aggregated selective match kernel (R-ASMK), which involves machine learning techniques and could potentially fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for text-based retrieval, which could fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning models, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
